.TH "TEMPORAL.PLAINYEARMONTH.CALENDARID" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.PlainYearMonth.calendarId \-
Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype.calendarId
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]calendarId\f[B]\f[R] accessor property of
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainYearMonth\f[R] instances returns a string
representing the calendar used to interpret the internal ISO 8601 date.
.PP
See \f[CR]Intl.supportedValuesOf()\f[R] for a list of commonly supported
calendar types.
.PP
The set accessor of \f[CR]calendarId\f[R] is \f[CR]undefined\f[R].
You cannot change this property directly.
There\(cqs no obvious way to create a new
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainYearMonth\f[R] object with a different calendar that
represents the same year\-month, so you need to convert it to a
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R] object first using
\f[CR]toPlainDate()\f[R], change the calendar, and then convert it back.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using calendarId
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] ym = Temporal.PlainYearMonth.from(\(dq2021\-07\(dq);
console.log(ym.calendarId); \f[I]// \(dqiso8601\(dq; default\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] ym2 = Temporal.PlainYearMonth.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01[u\-ca=chinese]\(dq);
console.log(ym2.calendarId); \f[I]// \(dqchinese\(dq\f[R]
.EE
.SS Changing calendarId
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] ym = Temporal.PlainYearMonth.from(\(dq2021\-07\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] newYM = ym
  .toPlainDate({ day: 1 })
  .withCalendar(\(dqchinese\(dq)
  .toPlainYearMonth();
console.log(newYM.year, newYM.monthCode); \f[I]// 2021 \(dqM05\(dq\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] newYM2 = ym
  .toPlainDate({ day: 31 })
  .withCalendar(\(dqchinese\(dq)
  .toPlainYearMonth();
console.log(newYM2.year, newYM2.monthCode); \f[I]// 2021 \(dqM06\(dq\f[R]
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainYearMonth\f[R]
